"I'm glad you reminded me," Chet called out. "I had clean forgotten about them."\par
The others laughed. In his desk at school, Chet had a small calendar, and as each day passed he carefully stroked out the date and hopefully counted the days that remained before vacation.\par
"What say we go camping when the holidays come?" he suggested.\par
"Camping!" Frank exclaimed. "Camping is for summer time."\par
"Just as much fun in winter. There are lots of shacks and cottages along shore. We could rent one for a couple of weeks. One with a fireplace and a stove. With lots of firewood and blankets and grub we'd be as comfortable as we could wish-and tbink of the fun we'd have ice-boating."\par
"Say, that's a mighty good idea," ventured Joe. "Sometimes you do use your head for something besides putting your hat on it. What do you think, Frank?"\par
"I think that Chet has had a real idea-for once in his life."\par
Chet grinned good-naturadely at this chaff of his comrades.\par
"Well, if it's a good idea, let's carry it through."\par
Further discussion of the proposal was interrupted just then by the appearance of two\par
